The paper introduces a new generative model that uses score matching to estimate gradients of the data distribution, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model is applied to image datasets such as MNIST, CelebA, and CIFAR-10, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions that the model architecture is flexible, which suggests that it may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Langevin dynamics and noise perturbation in the model also suggests that it may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory), respectively.
